<br>
<br>
Heh. I know some EQ players use www.strike9.com for hosting images. If you use dial-up, you should see how much Web space is given to you in your package. Most often ISPs like Earthlink give you some storage, and then all you need to do is use an FTP client to upload images to your own site. Same with DSL or Cable service. Find out what is included. You can also sign up for a service like Homestead. They have a free trial period. I like "free" services, but in reality there is some hidden cost or downside to pay for the bandwidth.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>and 2nd, how the heck can i make a sig. i tried photoshop, and it confuses the hell outa me</i><br>
<br>
Well to get basic proficiency in Photoshop you really do need to sit down and do the tutorial and learn how to use the different tools, layers, and masks. If you don't want to do that, then try a more-consumer-friendly app like the image editing tools that come with Windows (if you know nothing about image editing). Play around with the apps until you think you know what you're doing then move up to Photoshop. By the way, I also use GIMP (www.gimp.org) for Windows. It's free and although the interface takes some time, it is just as effective as Photoshop without the huge expense for a legal license. <br>
<br>
Some tips: Antialias text in images or the text turns out too jagged and icky-looking. Save your bitmap under a new name every time you add an element or make a change. Play with different JPEG conversion rates from BMP files -- JPEG is always lossy -- you want a small file size and good looks. BMP has no loss of image quality, but the file sizes are TOO BIG; nobody wants to see your 2MB sig. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucloudien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cloudien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/02 8:21:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1350.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sigs</span><hr size=1> I love to see GIMP being widely recognised on this board.. who said open source was dead <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->                                 (Oh yeah, Bill Gates)<br>
